⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Thorby Baslim-Rudbek
node H1 · H1 · ⟦Thorby Baslim-Rudbek:H1:b0bec4⟧

WHO   — A scarred, half-feral beggar boy on the slave-block of Jubbulpore, bought for a trifling sum by an old crippled mendicant — who turns out to be far more than a beggar, and who leaves the boy a destiny he never sought.
WHAT  — The runaway thread of Citizen of the Galaxy — sold as a slave, raised by a spy, adopted by Free Traders, conscripted by the Guard, and at last revealed as Thor Bradley Rudbek, lost heir to the greatest shipbuilding fortune in the Terran sphere.
WHERE — From the slave-market of Jubbulpore to the Free Trader ship Sisu, to Hekate and the Terran Guard, and home to the Rudbek estate on Earth.
WHY   — Because the old man who freed him spent his life fighting the slave trade — and a debt of love, once owed, is paid by taking up the cause: to turn an inherited empire against the very traffic that once sold him.
HOW   — By obedience that becomes loyalty, by learning each world's rules and then outgrowing them, and finally by claiming the boardroom power to fight slavers from the top down.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A free man owes the man who freed him — and pays it forward by freeing the rest.

